
[1]cruel

   CRUEL, a. [L. See Crude and Rude.]

   1. Disposed to give pain to others, in body or mind; willing or pleased
   to torment, vex or afflict; inhuman; destitute of pity, compassion or
   kindness; fierce; ferocious; savage; barbarous; hardhearted; applied to
   persons or their dispositions.

   They are cruel, and have no mercy. Jeremiah 6.

   2. Inhuman; barbarous; savage; causing pain, grief or distress; exerted
   in tormenting, vexing or afflicting.

   Cursed be their wrath, for it was cruel. Genesis 44.

   The tender mercies of the wicked are cruel. Proverbs 12.

   Others had trials of cruel mockings. Hebrews 11.
